{"id": "1440513125484068925", "channel_id": "1440128900490330182", "author_id": "178332860464234498", "author_name": "raumbobulus", "content": "Supporting this, I agree with all of the points mentioned above. I’ve been really enjoying the game since I started around a week ago and the story, lore, etc. is amazing, and it feels frustrating having to open up the dialogue history in the top right just to reread what someone said because I tapped twice on accident and the game auto scrolled to the bottom of a block of text. It’s been a persistent issue for me in almost every chapter, and while I ignored it at first it really really started to disrupt the story for me as I got more and more invested in it, especially during key moments. Either increasing  the size of the visible text box so it can fit more text or just adding a scroll bar to the dialogue so I can scroll back up instead of being stuck at the bottom of a paragraph would be immensely helpful", "timestamp": "2025-11-19T01:24:52.555000+00:00", "thread_id": "1440128900490330182"}
